    "persona": "NEW_ADMIN",
    "question": "How do I activate my Acronis account after receiving the email?",
    "expected_answerable": true,
    "agent_answer": "## Activating Your Acronis Account\n\nWhen an administrator creates an account for you, you'll receive an email containing:\n\n1. **Your login** (username) — also shown on the account activation page.\n2. An **\"Activate account\"** button.\n\n### Steps to activate:\n\n1. Open the email and click the **Activate account** button.\n2. Set a password for your account — it must be **at least 9 characters long**.\n3. Once activated, you can log in to the **Cyber Protect console**:\n   - Go to the Cyber Protection login page.\n   - Enter your login and click **Next**.\n   - Enter your password and click **Next**.\n   - If you use more than one Cyber Protect Cloud service, select **Cyber Protection**.\n\n### Recommended: Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)\n\nAfter activation, consider setting up **2FA** for additional security. This requires a one-time code from an authenticator app on your mobile device, protecting your account even if your password is compromised.\n\n---\n\n📄 **Sources:** `01-activating-account.md`, `05-accessing-cyber-protection-service.md`, `03-two-factor-authentication.md`",
