    "question": "How do I reset my password if I forgot it after activation?",
    "expected_answerable": false,
    "agent_answer": "Based on the retrieved documentation, I don't have specific instructions for the **\"Forgot Password\"** reset flow after account activation.\n\nHowever, here's what the documentation does cover that may help:\n\n1. **Login page**: You access the Cyber Protection service via the Cyber Protect console login page. Typically, most login pages include a **\"Forgot password?\"** link — look for this on the login screen when you type your login and click **Next**.\n\n2. **Account activation**: During initial activation, you set your password via the **\"Activate account\"** button in the email you received. The password must be **at least 9 characters long** (per the activation docs).\n\n3. **Two-factor authentication (2FA)**: If 2FA is enabled on your account, you'll also need access to your authenticator app after resetting your password.\n\n**Recommended steps:**\n- Go to the Cyber Protect console login page and look for a \"Forgot password\" or \"Reset password\" link.\n- If that option isn't available, contact your **service administrator** — they can reset your password or send a new activation link from the Management Portal.\n\n> **Sources:** `01-activating-account.md`, `05-accessing-cyber-protection-service.md`, `03-two-factor-authentication.md`",
