  {
    "id": "chunk_03_persona_NEW_ADMIN",
    "chunk_id": 3,
    "chunk_title": "Password requirements",
    "source_file": "02-password-requirements.md",
    "persona": "NEW_ADMIN",
    "question": "How do I set a password for a new user in Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud?",
    "expected_answerable": true,
    "agent_answer": "Based on the retrieved documentation, I don't have specific step-by-step instructions for setting a password for a new user in Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud.\n\nHowever, the documentation does mention that new users go through an **account activation** process. From the \"Accessing the Cyber Protection service\" document:\n\n> \"After you activate your account, you can access the Cyber Protection service by logging in to the Cyber Protect console or via Management Portal.\"\n\nTypically in Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud, when a new user account is created by an administrator, the user receives an **activation email** with a link to set their password. The general flow is:\n\n1. An administrator creates the user account in the **Management Portal**.\n2. The new user receives an **activation email**.\n3. The user clicks the activation link and **sets their own password**.\n4. After activation, they can log in to the Cyber Protect console.\n\nAdditionally, if **two-factor authentication (2FA)** is enabled for the organization, the user will also need to set up a one-time code generator app on their device after setting their password.\n\n> *\"When 2FA is set up, you are required to enter your password (the first factor) and a one-time code (the second factor) to log in to the Cyber Protect console.\"*\n> — Source: `03-two-factor-authentication.md`\n\nFor detailed instructions on creating user accounts and managing passwords, I'd recommend checking the **Management Portal** section of the Acronis documentation, which was not included in the retrieved context.\n\n**Sources:** `05-accessing-cyber-protection-service.md`, `03-two-factor-authentication.md`",
