  {
    "id": "chunk_03_persona_END_USER",
    "chunk_id": 3,
    "chunk_title": "Password requirements",
    "source_file": "02-password-requirements.md",
    "persona": "END_USER",
    "question": "I'm trying to create my account but it keeps saying my password is too weak even though it's really long, what's wrong?",
    "expected_answerable": true,
    "agent_answer": "## Password Weakness Despite Length\n\nHaving a long password doesn't guarantee it will be accepted. Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud checks password **complexity**, not just length. Your password is likely being rejected for one of these reasons:\n\n### Passwords always considered **weak** regardless of length:\n- **Repeats your user name or login**\n- **Repeats your email address**\n- **Repeats the name of your tenant** (the organization your account belongs to)\n- **Is a commonly used password** (e.g., \"Password123456!\", \"Qwerty12345678\", etc.)\n\n### What to do:\n1. Make sure your password is **at least 9 characters long**\n2. Ensure it does **not** contain your username, email, or tenant name\n3. Avoid common/dictionary passwords\n4. Aim for a password classified as **Medium** or **Strong** — you **cannot save a weak password** even if it meets the length requirement\n5. Mix uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and special characters in a non-predictable way\n\nOnce your password meets complexity requirements and is classified as at least \"Medium,\" you'll be able to proceed with account activation.\n\n---\n\n📄 *Sources: `02-password-requirements.md` (Password requirements), `01-activating-account.md` (Activating the account)*",
    "retrieved_chunks": [
      "02-password-requirements.md",
      "01-activating-account.md",
      "05-accessing-cyber-protection-service.md"
    ],
    "top_cosine_score": 0.74,
