    "no_results": false,
    "answer_cites_source": true
  },
  {
    "id": "chunk_03_persona_MANAGER",
    "chunk_id": 3,
    "chunk_title": "Password requirements",
    "source_file": "02-password-requirements.md",
    "persona": "MANAGER",
    "question": "What password strength levels does the platform enforce, and can users save a weak password if needed?",
    "expected_answerable": true,
    "agent_answer": "\n\nBased on the documentation, Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud classifies passwords into **three strength levels** during user registration:\n\n1. **Weak**\n2. **Medium**\n3. **Strong**\n\n**No, users cannot save a weak password**, even if it meets the minimum length requirement. Additionally, passwords are automatically considered **weak** if they:\n\n- Repeat the user name, login, or email\n- Repeat the name of the tenant the user account belongs to\n- Match most common passwords\n\n> **Note:** Password requirements are subject to change.\n\n**Source:** `02-password-requirements.md` — *Getting Started with Cyber Protection*",
