  {
    "id": "chunk_04_persona_NEW_ADMIN",
    "chunk_id": 4,
    "chunk_title": "Two-factor authentication",
    "source_file": "03-two-factor-authentication.md",
    "persona": "NEW_ADMIN",
    "question": "How do I set up two-factor authentication for my Acronis Cyber Protect account?",
    "expected_answerable": true,
    "agent_answer": "# Setting Up Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)\n\nTwo-factor authentication (2FA) provides additional protection from unauthorized access to your Acronis Cyber Protect account. Here's how it works:\n\n## How 2FA Works\n\nWhen 2FA is set up, you need **two things** to log in to the Cyber Protect console:\n\n1. **First factor:** Your password\n2. **Second factor:** A one-time code generated by a special authenticator application\n\nThis means that even if someone discovers your login and password, they will **not** be able to access your account without the one-time code from your device.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- You need to install an **authenticator application** on your mobile phone or another device that belongs to you (e.g., Google Authenticator, Microsoft Authenticator, etc.)\n\n## Logging In with 2FA Enabled\n\n1. Go to the Cyber Protection login page\n2. Type your **login**, then click **Next**\n3. Type your **password**, then click **Next**\n4. Enter the **one-time code** from your authenticator app\n\n> **Note:** The detailed step-by-step setup instructions (such as scanning the QR code and linking the authenticator app) may be configured by your administrator. If you need 2FA enabled or have trouble setting it up, contact your Acronis administrator.\n\n---\n\n**Sources:**\n- `03-two-factor-authentication.md` — *Getting Started with Cyber Protection*\n- `05-accessing-cyber-protection-service.md` — *Getting Started with Cyber Protection*",
    "retrieved_chunks": [
