    "expected_answerable": true,
    "agent_answer": "Based on the retrieved documentation, I don't have specific information about the TOTP code validity duration or what happens when the authenticator app's time is out of sync in Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud.\n\nThe documentation only covers the general concept of two-factor authentication (2FA) — that it requires a password (first factor) and a one-time code from an authenticator app (second factor) to log in to the Cyber Protect console.\n\n**General TOTP knowledge** (not from Acronis docs): Standard TOTP codes are typically valid for 30 seconds, and most systems accept codes within a small time window (±1 interval) to account for minor clock drift. However, I cannot confirm whether Acronis follows this standard or has its own specific behavior.\n\nFor precise details, I'd recommend:\n1. Checking the full Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud admin guide on 2FA configuration\n2. Contacting Acronis support directly\n\n**Source:** `03-two-factor-authentication.md` (Getting Started with Cyber Protection)",
