    "question": "Can I use two-factor authentication to protect individual backup plans or recovery operations?",
    "expected_answerable": false,
    "agent_answer": "Based on the retrieved documentation, **no** — two-factor authentication (2FA) in Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud is designed to protect **account access**, not individual backup plans or recovery operations.\n\nSpecifically, 2FA works at the **login level**:\n\n- When 2FA is enabled, you must enter your **password** (first factor) and a **one-time code** (second factor) to **log in to the Cyber Protect console**.\n- The one-time code is generated by an authenticator app installed on your mobile device.\n- Its purpose is to prevent unauthorized access to your account even if your credentials are compromised.\n\nThere is no mention in the documentation of applying 2FA granularly to specific backup plans or recovery operations. It is an **account-wide security measure** that protects access to the console itself.\n\n**Source:** `03-two-factor-authentication.md` — *Getting Started with Cyber Protection*",
