    "expected_answerable": true,
    "agent_answer": "## Turning Off Google Analytics in Cyber Protect Cloud\n\nBased on the documentation, Cyber Protect Cloud has **Privacy settings** that allow you to control the collection, use, and disclosure of your personal information, including Google Analytics.\n\nHere's what you need to know:\n\n- **On initial launch**, depending on your country and the data center serving you, you may be asked to confirm whether you agree to use Google Analytics.\n- You can indicate whether or not you give consent through the **Privacy settings** in the Cyber Protect Cloud console.\n\nTo manage this, navigate to the **Privacy settings** section within the Cyber Protect Cloud console, where you can withdraw or modify your consent for Google Analytics data collection.\n\n> **Note:** The available privacy options may vary depending on your region and the Cyber Protect Cloud data center providing services to you.\n\n---\n\n📄 *Source: `04-privacy-settings.md` — Getting Started with Cyber Protection*",
