    "agent_answer": "I don't have specific documentation available on configuring Data Loss Prevention (DLP) policies in Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud.\n\nHowever, here's what I can share at a high level:\n\n**Acronis Advanced DLP (Device Control / Data Loss Prevention)** is typically available as an **add-on pack** within Cyber Protect Cloud. To configure it, you would generally:\n\n1. **Enable the Advanced DLP pack** on the tenant/customer level in the management console.\n2. **Create or edit a protection plan** and look for the **Device Control** or **Data Loss Prevention** module.\n3. **Define policies** that control:\n   - Which device types are allowed/blocked (USB drives, printers, clipboard, etc.)\n   - Content-aware rules (sensitive data patterns like credit card numbers, SSNs, etc.)\n   - Allowlists/blocklists for specific devices\n4. **Apply the protection plan** to the target workloads/machines.\n\n**For accurate, step-by-step instructions, I recommend:**\n- Checking the official **Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud Administrator Guide** at [https://www.acronis.com/support/documentation/](https://www.acronis.com/support/documentation/)\n- Contacting **Acronis Support** or your service provider for guidance specific to your console version\n- Reviewing the **Advanced DLP** section in the Acronis Knowledge Base at [https://kb.acronis.com](https://kb.acronis.com)\n\nI apologize that I couldn't provide more detailed documentation on this specific topic. Would you like help with another Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud feature?",
