    "agent_answer": "I don't have specific documentation in my knowledge base about password reset procedures for Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud. However, here are the general steps you can try:\n\n## Password Reset Options\n\n1. **Self-Service Reset (Most Common):**\n   - Go to your Acronis Cyber Protect Cloud login page\n   - Click **\"Forgot password?\"** link below the login fields\n   - Enter your registered email address\n   - Check your email for a password reset link\n   - Follow the link to set a new password\n\n2. **If you're a technician/end-user:**\n   - Contact your **service provider (MSP)** — they can reset your password from the management portal\n\n3. **If you're a partner admin:**\n   - Contact **Acronis Support** directly or your distributor to get your account unlocked/reset\n\n4. **If it's the protection agent password (not the web console):**\n   - The agent typically authenticates through the cloud console credentials. Re-registering the agent with valid credentials may be needed.\n\n## Important Notes\n- Password reset links usually **expire within a few hours**\n- Check your **spam/junk folder** if you don't see the reset email\n- If your account is locked due to too many failed attempts, you may need to wait or contact your administrator\n\n**For the fastest resolution, contact your service provider or Acronis support directly**, as they can reset your credentials from the admin console.\n\n*Note: No specific documentation was found in the knowledge base for this topic. The above is general guidance.*",
